r 16|ja|10月16日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – The {{ill|Battle of Itsukushima|ja|厳島の戦い|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} took place, with the forces of {{ill|Mōri Motonari|ja|Mōri Motonari|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} defeating those of {{ill|Tōharaken|ja|陶晴賢|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} . * {{ill|Tenshō|ja|天正|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)|lt=Tenshō Era|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 15th Year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1587 AD|ja|1587th year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|November 1|ja|11月1日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – The Kitano Grand Tea Ceremony was held in Kyoto’s {{ill|Kitano Tenmangū|ja|Kitano Tenmangu Shrine|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} precincts, where {{ill|Toyotomi Hideyoshi|ja|豊臣秀吉|1=Toyotomi Hideyoshi|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , with tea masters {{ill|Sen no Rikyū|ja|千利休|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , {{ill|Tsuda Sōkyū|ja|津田宗及|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , and {{ill|Imai Sōkyū|ja|今井宗久|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , presided over a gathering of 1,000 participants. * {{ill|Keichō|ja|Keichō|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 19th Year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1614 AD|ja|1614th year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|November 2|ja|11月2日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – {{ill|Tokugawa Ieyasu|ja|徳川家康|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ordered various daimyō to mobilize, marking the beginning of the Osaka Winter Campaign. * {{ill|Enpō|ja|延宝|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st Year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1673 AD|ja|1673rd year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|November 9|ja|11月9日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – The {{ill|Iwakuni Domain|ja|岩国藩|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} constructed the {{ill|Kintaikyo Bridge|ja|錦帯橋|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} .
== Deaths == * {{ill|Kōji|ja|Kōji|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st Year ( {{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1555 AD|ja|1555th year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|October 16|ja|10月16日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – {{ill|Tōharaken|ja|陶晴賢|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , a military commander (born {{ill|1521 AD|ja|1521st year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ). * {{ill|Keichō|ja|Keichō|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 5th Year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1600 AD|ja|1600th year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|November 6|ja|11月6日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – {{ill|Ishida Mitsunari|ja|石田三成|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , a military commander (born {{ill|1560 AD|ja|1560th year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ). * {{ill|Keichō|ja|Keichō|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 5th Year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1600 AD|ja|1600th year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|November 6|ja|11月6日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – {{ill|Konishi Yukinaga|ja|Konishi Yukinaga|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , a Christian daimyō (born circa {{ill|1555 AD|ja|1555th year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ?). * {{ill|Keichō|ja|Keichō|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 5th Year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1600 AD|ja|1600th year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|November 6|ja|11月6日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – {{ill|Angokuji Eikyū|ja|安国寺恵瓊|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , a military commander (born circa {{ill|1539 AD|ja|1539th year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ?).
