{{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=十月初一|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 10월 1일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar October|qq=}} '''October 1''' is the 1st day of month {{ill|October (Lunisolar)|ja|10月 (旧暦)|lt=October (Kannazuki)|1=Kannazuki|2=ja|3=10月 (旧暦)|1=Kannazuki|qq=}} the 10th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}} . It's {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=}} day is {{ill|Butsumetsu|ja|仏滅|qq=}} .
== Events == * {{ill|Emperor Tenmu|ja|Emperor Tenmu|1=Emperor Tenmu|qq=}} 13th Year ( {{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=}} {{ill|684 AD|ja|684th year|qq=}} {{ill|November 13|ja|11月13日|qq=}} ) – Established the eight types of surnames: Mahito, Asomi, Sukune, Kisune, Dōshi, Omi, Ren, and Inaoki. {{要出典|date=2021-04|qq=}} * {{ill|Shuchō|ja|朱鳥|qq=}} 1st Year ( {{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=}} {{ill|686 AD|ja|686th year|qq=}} {{ill|October 23|ja|10月23日|qq=}} ) – {{ill|Prince Ōtsu|ja|大津皇子|qq=}} was captured by Crown Prince {{ill|Kusakabe|ja|草壁皇子|qq=}} on suspicion of treason. * {{ill|Hōki|ja|宝亀|qq=}} 1st Year ( {{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=}} {{ill|770 AD|ja|770th year|qq=}} {{ill|October 23|ja|10月23日|qq=}} ) – By the presentation of Suikime, the era was changed from {{ill|Shingokeiun|ja|神護景雲|qq=}} to Hōki. * {{ill|Hōki|ja|宝亀|qq=}} 1st Year ( {{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=}} {{ill|770 AD|ja|770th year|qq=}} {{ill|October 23|ja|10月23日|qq=}} ) – The grandson of {{ill|Emperor Tenji|ja|天智天皇|qq=}} , Prince Shirakabe, ascended to the throne as the 49th Emperor, {{ill|Emperor Kōnin|ja|光仁天皇|qq=}} . * {{ill|Kōji|ja|Kōji|qq=}} 1st Year ( {{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=}} {{ill|1555 AD|ja|1555th year|qq=}} {{ill|October 16|ja|10月16日|qq=}} ) – The {{ill|Battle of Itsukushima|ja|厳島の戦い|qq=}} took place, with the forces of {{ill|Mōri Motonari|ja|Mōri Motonari|qq=}} defeating those of {{ill|Tōharaken|ja|陶晴賢|qq=}} . * {{ill|Tenshō|ja|天正|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)|lt=Tenshō Era|qq=}} 15th Year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=}} {{ill|1587 AD|ja|1587th year|qq=}} {{ill|November 1|ja|11月1日|qq=}} ) – The Kitano Grand Tea Ceremony was held in Kyoto’s {{ill|Kitano Tenmangū|ja|Kitano Tenmangu Shrine|qq=}} precincts, where {{ill|Toyotomi Hideyoshi|ja|豊臣秀吉|1=Toyotomi Hideyoshi|qq=}} , with tea masters {{ill|Sen no Rikyū|ja|千利休|qq=}} , {{ill|Tsuda Sōkyū|ja|津田宗及|qq=}} , and {{ill|Imai Sōkyū|ja|今井宗久|qq=}} , presided over a gathering of 1,000 participants. * {{ill|Keichō|ja|Keichō|qq=}} 19th Year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=}} {{ill|1614 AD|ja|1614th year|qq=}} {{ill|November 2|ja|11月2日|qq=}} ) – {{ill|Tokugawa Ieyasu|ja|徳川家康|qq=}} ordered various daimyō to mobilize, marking the beginning of the Osaka Winter Campaign. * {{ill|Enpō|ja|延宝|qq=}} 1st Year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=}} {{ill|1673 AD|ja|1673rd year|qq=}} {{ill|November 9|ja|11月9日|qq=}} ) – The {{ill|Iwakuni Domain|ja|岩国藩|qq=}} constructed the {{ill|Kintaikyo Bridge|ja|錦帯橋|qq=}} .
== Deaths == * {{ill|Kōji|ja|Kōji|qq=}} 1st Year ( {{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=}} {{ill|1555 AD|ja|1555th year|qq=}} {{ill|October 16|ja|10月16日|qq=}} ) – {{ill|Tōharaken|ja|陶晴賢|qq=}} , a military commander (born {{ill|1521 AD|ja|1521st year|qq=}} ). * {{ill|Keichō|ja|Keichō|qq=}} 5th Year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=}} {{ill|1600 AD|ja|1600th year|qq=}} {{ill|November 6|ja|11月6日|qq=}} ) – {{ill|Ishida Mitsunari|ja|石田三成|qq=}} , a military commander (born {{ill|1560 AD|ja|1560th year|qq=}} ). * {{ill|Keichō|ja|Keichō|qq=}} 5th Year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=}} {{ill|1600 AD|ja|1600th year|qq=}} {{ill|November 6|ja|11月6日|qq=}} ) – {{ill|Konishi Yukinaga|ja|Konishi Yukinaga|qq=}} , a Christian daimyō (born circa {{ill|1555 AD|ja|1555th year|qq=}} ?). * {{ill|Keichō|ja|Keichō|qq=}} 5th Year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=}} {{ill|1600 AD|ja|1600th year|qq=}} {{ill|November 6|ja|11月6日|qq=}} ) – {{ill|Angokuji Eikyū|ja|安国寺恵瓊|qq=}} , a military commander (born circa {{ill|1539 AD|ja|1539th year|qq=}} ?).
