== Events == * {{ill|Emperor Tenmu|ja|Emperor Tenmu|1=Emperor Tenmu|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Tenmu|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Tenmu|qq=}} 13th Year ( [[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:684|684 AD]] [[:en:November 13|November 13]] ) – Established the eight types of surnames: Mahito, Asomi, Sukune, Kisune, Dōshi, Omi, Ren, and Inaoki. {{Citation needed|date=2021-04|qq=}} * [[:en:Shuchō|Shuchō]] 1st Year ( [[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:686|686 AD]] [[:en:October 23|October 23]] ) – [[:en:Prince Ōtsu|Prince Ōtsu]] was captured by Crown Prince [[:en:Prince Kusakabe|Kusakabe]] on suspicion of treason. * [[:en:Hōki|Hōki]] 1st Year ( [[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:770|770 AD]] [[:en:October 23|October 23]] ) – By the presentation of Suikime, the era was changed from [[:en:Jingo-keiun|Shingokeiun]] to Hōki. * [[:en:Hōki|Hōki]] 1st Year ( [[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:770|770 AD]] [[:en:October 23|October 23]] ) – The grandson of [[:en:Emperor Tenji|Emperor Tenji]] , Prince Shirakabe, ascended to the throne as the 49th Emperor, [[:en:Emperor Kōnin|Emperor Kōnin]] . * {{ill|Kōji|ja|Kōji|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōji|qq=}} 1st Year ( [[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1555|1555 AD]] [[:en:October 16|October 16]] ) – The [[:en:Battle of Miyajima|Battle of Itsukushima]] took place, with the forces of {{ill|Mōri Motonari|ja|Mōri Motonari|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mōri Motonari|qq=}} defeating those of [[:en:Sue Harukata|Tōharaken]] . * [[:en:Tenshō (Momoyama period)|Tenshō Era]] 15th Year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1587|1587 AD]] [[:en:November 1|November 1]] ) – The Kitano Grand Tea Ceremony was held in Kyoto’s {{ill|Kitano Tenmangū|ja|Kitano Tenmangu Shrine|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kitano Tenmangū|qq=}} precincts, where [[:en:Toyotomi Hideyoshi|Toyotomi Hideyoshi]] , with tea masters [[:en:Sen no Rikyū|Sen no Rikyū]] , [[:en:Tsuda Sōgyū|Tsuda Sōkyū]] , and [[:en:Imai Sōkyū|Imai Sōkyū]] , presided over a gathering of 1,000 participants. * {{ill|Keichō|1=Keichō|2=ja|3=慶長|ja|Keichō|1=Keichō|2=ja|3=慶長|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Keichō|qq=}} 19th Year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1614|1614 AD]] [[:en:November 2|November 2]] ) – [[:en:Tokugawa Ieyasu|Tokugawa Ieyasu]] ordered various daimyō to mobilize, marking the beginning of the Osaka Winter Campaign. * [[:en:Enpō|Enpō]] 1st Year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1673|1673 AD]] [[:en:November 9|November 9]] ) – The [[:en:Iwakuni Domain|Iwakuni Domain]] constructed the [[:en:Kintai Bridge|Kintaikyo Bridge]] .
== Deaths == * {{ill|Kōji|ja|Kōji|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōji|qq=}} 1st Year ( [[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1555|1555 AD]] [[:en:October 16|October 16]] ) – [[:en:Sue Harukata|Tōharaken]] , a military commander (born [[:en:1521|1521 AD]] ). * {{ill|Keichō|1=Keichō|2=ja|3=慶長|ja|Keichō|1=Keichō|2=ja|3=慶長|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Keichō|qq=}} 5th Year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1600|1600 AD]] [[:en:November 6|November 6]] ) – [[:en:Ishida Mitsunari|Ishida Mitsunari]] , a military commander (born [[:en:1560|1560 AD]] ). * {{ill|Keichō|1=Keichō|2=ja|3=慶長|ja|Keichō|1=Keichō|2=ja|3=慶長|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Keichō|qq=}} 5th Year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1600|1600 AD]] [[:en:November 6|November 6]] ) – {{ill|Konishi Yukinaga|ja|Konishi Yukinaga|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Konishi Yukinaga|qq=}} , a Christian daimyō (born circa [[:en:1555|1555 AD]] ?). * {{ill|Keichō|1=Keichō|2=ja|3=慶長|ja|Keichō|1=Keichō|2=ja|3=慶長|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Keichō|qq=}} 5th Year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1600|1600 AD]] [[:en:November 6|November 6]] ) – [[:en:Ankokuji Ekei|Angokuji Eikyū]] , a military commander (born circa [[:en:1539|1539 AD]] ?).
