* {{ill|Hōki|en|Hōki|WD=Q18520676|lt=Hōki|1=Hōki}}  1st Year ( {{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|WD=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}}  {{ill|770|en|770|WD=Q25021|lt=770 AD|1=770}}  {{ill|October 23|en|October 23|WD=Q2958|lt=October 23|1=October 23}} ) – By the presentation of Suikime, the era was changed from {{ill|Jingo-keiun|en|Jingo-keiun|WD=Q1373049|lt=Shingokeiun|1=Jingo-keiun}}  to Hōki.
* {{ill|Hōki|en|Hōki|WD=Q18520676|lt=Hōki|1=Hōki}}  1st Year ( {{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|WD=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}}  {{ill|770|en|770|WD=Q25021|lt=770 AD|1=770}}  {{ill|October 23|en|October 23|WD=Q2958|lt=October 23|1=October 23}} ) – The grandson of {{ill|Emperor Tenji|en|Emperor Tenji|WD=Q314802|lt=Emperor Tenji|1=Emperor Tenji}} , Prince Shirakabe, ascended to the throne as the 49th Emperor, {{ill|Emperor Kōnin|en|Emperor Kōnin|WD=Q958662|lt=Emperor Kōnin|1=Emperor Kōnin}} .
* {{ill|Kōji|ja|Kōji|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōji|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}  1st Year ( {{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|WD=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}}  {{ill|1555|en|1555|WD=Q6579|lt=1555 AD|1=1555}}  {{ill|October 16|en|October 16|WD=Q2963|lt=October 16|1=October 16}} ) – The {{ill|Battle of Miyajima|en|Battle of Miyajima|WD=Q1064989|lt=Battle of Itsukushima|1=Battle of Miyajima}}  took place, with the forces of {{ill|Mōri Motonari|1=Mōri Motonari|2=ja|3=毛利元就|ja|Mōri Motonari|1=Mōri Motonari|2=ja|3=毛利元就|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mōri Motonari|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q1156545}}  defeating those of {{ill|Sue Harukata|en|Sue Harukata|WD=Q842653|lt=Tōharaken|1=Sue Harukata}} .
* {{ill|Tenshō (Momoyama period)|en|Tenshō (Momoyama period)|WD=Q1145058|lt=Tenshō Era|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)}}  15th Year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}}  {{ill|1587|en|1587|WD=Q6744|lt=1587 AD|1=1587}}  {{ill|November 1|en|November 1|WD=Q2997|lt=November 1|1=November 1}} ) – The Kitano Grand Tea Ceremony was held in Kyoto’s {{ill|Kitano Tenmangū|ja|Kitano Tenmangu Shrine|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kitano Tenmangū|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}  precincts, where {{ill|Toyotomi Hideyoshi|en|Toyotomi Hideyoshi|WD=Q187550|lt=Toyotomi Hideyoshi|1=Toyotomi Hideyoshi}} , with tea masters {{ill|Sen no Rikyū|en|Sen no Rikyū|WD=Q305477|lt=Sen no Rikyū|1=Sen no Rikyū}} , {{ill|Tsuda Sōgyū|en|Tsuda Sōgyū|WD=Q7849927|lt=Tsuda Sōkyū|1=Tsuda Sōgyū}} , and {{ill|Imai Sōkyū|en|Imai Sōkyū|WD=Q6002963|lt=Imai Sōkyū|1=Imai Sōkyū}} , presided over a gathering of 1,000 participants.
